MeanUnitaryCurrent\
\
Calculates the mean current for each event in an events list.\
\
INPUT:\
events list (.txt)\
.abf file (saved as int)\
\
DETAIL\
This particular script adds the current measurement directly before and after events that are classified as \'931\'94 in the events list (See lines 100 and 126). This was done for analysis of TRAAK currents, where open events classified as \'931\'94 were short and the threshold cutoff used in the events list omitted these values. A set of three scripts are included \'93.._first_open\'94, \'93.._second_open\'94, \'93.._all_open\'94 which pads open events classified as \'931\'94, \'931 and 2\'94, and all nonzero events with adjacent values before and after the time cutoff.\
\
OUTPUT:\
Eventslist_2_Histogram_1adjacent.csv\
